- Peak mode should only affect file pickup and temporary file location before processing.

Why HDFS rename is used:
File eligibility/status is managed through HDFS file operations, not a DB file-status table. Therefore, duplicate prevention should be done using HDFS rename/move.

Duplicate prevention requirement:
- In peak mode, selected files are moved out of the input directory before processing.
- The next CPP trigger should list only the normal input/pending directory.
- Since previously selected files are now under _peak_mode_processing/<application_id>, the next trigger should not pick them.
- If another overlapping CPP application already moved a file, HDFS rename should fail. Log the failure and skip that file.
- Only successfully renamed files should be processed.

